            %i Beza Tekola, Washington DC  |  Bridesmaid
            %p Beza and I have known each other for 15 years! Our friendship has withstood the test of time and distance. Our journey has been one of love and respect.  Although many miles have separated us once we graduated college we have always remained close by visiting each other whenever we can and through long phone conversations that often leaves us in tears from laughter! Beza has always been and will always be one of my dearest friends.               
          %hr
      .row
        .col-sm-4
          =image_tag'martha.jpg', class: 'img-circle wedding-party-image gm1'
        .col-sm-6
          %span.gm1-text
            %i Martha Getachew, Addis Ababa  |  Bridesmaid
            %p Martha and I first met each other in Atlanta in 2011 and have been friends since. She is a woman with a kind heart and warm smile! Even though she moved to Addis and I was living in ATL you will often find us chatting on gchat no matter what time of the day. Then as faith would have it I also moved to Addis. Terrified of making new friends it’s been a blessing having Martha by my side to have fun with. She is someone who always makes me laugh and I look forward to creating new memories through our new adventures.        
          %hr
      .row  
        .col-sm-4
          =image_tag'meskerem.jpg', class: 'img-circle wedding-party-image gm1'
        .col-sm-6
          %span.gm1-text
            %i Meskerm Woldegebrel, Toronto, Canada  |  Bridesmaid
            %p Meki and I are cousins! She’s known me almost all my life and understands my journey in life more than others. We have a bond that’s unbroken by distance and I know I can always count on her no matter what. She knows how to make me smile and motivate me through the tough times of life. She’s someone I look up to as an inspiration for strengthen and unconditional love. I am beyond excited to have her celebrate with us our wedding day. Especially since she and Weyni (his cousin) were the ones that introduced us. They will always have a special place in our love story and in our hearts.        
          %hr
      .row  
        .col-sm-4
          =image_tag'image1.JPG', class: 'img-circle wedding-party-image gm1'
        .col-sm-6
          %span.gm1-text
            %i Fikerte G/Kiros “Kuku”, Seattle  |  Bridesmaid
            %p Kuku is not only my future sister-in law, but we have become friends since we first met a year ago. She’s fun to be around and has an easy going personality.  I first met her in Bahir Dar when she came to surprise her childhood friend for his wedding. She’s fun, loving, and considerate. I quickly found out we are the same size and can share dresses and shoes!! It’s like finding my twin sister! I am excited to call her my family and feel blessed to have been accepted with open arms by her and the rest of Jawi’s family.  
          %hr
      .row  
        .col-sm-4
          =image_tag'sanaz.JPG', class: 'img-circle wedding-party-image gm1'
        .col-sm-6
          %span.gm1-text
            %i Sanaz Jalalat, Atlanta |  Bridesmaid
            %p Sanaz and I have known each other for over 15 years. She is my sister from another mother. Sanaz is one of the kindest, most thoughtful, and generous person I know. I can honestly say having her in my life has been one of the most important blessings I have received. At first she wasn’t going to make it to the wedding now that she’s able to join us with her husband I am beyond excited to have her by my side for the BIG day!  
          %hr    
